name: Stylish 4P Houseboat Apartment with Terrace & A/C
description:
Welcome aboard our brand new houseboat apartment, where modern comfort meets the tranquility of waterfront living!

Nestled along the shimmering waters, this charming retreat promises a unique getaway experience like no other.

Whether you're seeking a romantic escape or a peaceful retreat with loved ones, our houseboat apartment provides the perfect blend of luxury and serenity for an unforgettable stay.

Come experience the magic of waterfront living with us!

Please note that there is AC!
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to the charming neighborhood IJsbaanpad and the iconic Olympic Stadium in Amsterdam – a delightful blend of tranquility and convenience, ensuring an unforgettable stay in the heart of this vibrant city.

Nestled amidst leafy streets and picturesque canals, this neighborhood offers a peaceful retreat away from the hustle and bustle of the city center. Take leisurely strolls along the tranquil waterways or explore the nearby parks, where lush greenery provides a serene backdrop for relaxation and rejuvenation.

For sports enthusiasts and history buffs alike, the proximity to the historic Olympic Stadium is a true highlight. Immerse yourself in the rich sporting heritage of Amsterdam as you discover the iconic venue that hosted the 1928 Summer Olympics.

Whether you're attending a sporting event, exploring the stadium's museum, or simply admiring its striking architecture, the Olympic Stadium is sure to leave a lasting impression.

Despite

I live in Amsterdam on a houseboat with my wife, and I love wildlife photography, traveling, food, hiking, woodcraft, and motorcycling,

Looking forward to connecting with you!

Enjoy Life.

neighborhood_overview: Dappermarkt is one of the country’s oldest - and best - outdoor markets. It forms the multicultural heart of the neighbourhood along with such major arteries as Javastraat, which once only provided every manner of global grocery but is now beginning to feature more upscale cafes and terraces. One of the city’s largest general hospitals, OLVG, is also located here. Two stellar city parks, Oosterpark and Flevopark, provide quick escape from the relatively busy streets. Besides many cheap ethnic eateries and supermarkets, the area is attracting much more higher-end cafes and restaurants who are often re-inventing many of the area’s industrial monuments. On sunny days, the parks and terraces are filled with nice people.

name: Cosy family house in quiet Amsterdam Noord
description:
We live in a spacious house, in a quiet family area in Amsterdam Noord. Our home has a relaxed and spacious living room and a fully equipped kitchen with all you will need to enjoy an evening at home. In the kitchen, the door opens to our shady and green garden.
On the 1st floor you will find our bathroom, and 3 bedrooms: one with a double bed, and two toddler rooms with children beds. Our bathroom has a shower, a bath and toilet. On the second floor there is another bedroom with a double bed.
neighborhood_overview:
Our house lies in between the ‘Vliegenbos’ (forrest) and ‘Noorderpark’; both great places for a walk or morningrun. Don’t forget to stop by at ‘Pompet’ in the Noorderpark for coffee/lunch or dinner.

Within 5 minutes you can walk to the lovely ‘Nieuwendammerdijk’ where you will enjoy a friendly village vibe & beautiful characteristic dike houses. Take a coffee or lunchbreak at ‘café ‘t Sluisje’ or cafe ‘Liever Hier’.

name: Big Warehouse apartment, Amsterdam
description:
I transformed a 250 m2 big industrial building into a creative playground for a group of friends. In Amsterdam North: the hip industrial area, where creativity is the new trend. You sleep in an old boatworkshop. It is designed to have fun.
There are 18 beds throughout the building.
neighborhood_overview:
The North of Amsterdam is a very trendy industrial area with a lot of artistic places to drink and dine in the neighbourhood. There is a good coffeshop at about 100 meters. A good Thai restaurant and Chinese takeaway around the corner.
Go to: De Ceuvel about 200 meters from the appartment. Go there for a nice breakfast or evening dinner and drinks in a super cool place.
Or go to de NDSM WHARF an old ship wharf with cafes/ restaurants like "Noorderlicht" or "Pllek": a restaurant built of old containers!
dont'forget to visit the centre of Amsterdam from time to time.

description:
In an industrial building I created a spacious apartment in its former industrial style. It's like you are staying in a workshop. Oil-drum kitchen, rusty chandelier, old wooden bar, beds made of scaffolding wood, chains and paint cans everywhere.
You will also find an (amateur-) pool table, double showers for romantic showers together and a terrace with BBQ in front of the building. There also is a free private parking space. And last but not least you will have your own roof terrace!!

Shopping center Mosplein is 200 meters from the apartment , there you,ll find 2 big supermarkets.
A coffeeshop is only 100 meters away ( to buy all sorts off smokeries)
And a Chinese take away is next door.
The Ceuvel across the street and canal. For diner and lunch. It has a good bar as well. Great atmosphere.
Also the NDSM , is 500 meters to the left. To the end of the Papaverweg. A Big creative industrial terrain with good bars and restaurants like Noorderlicht or PLLEK with good food in a creative restaurant . You have never seen a restaurant like this. name: Your Home - City Apartment in Amsterdam
description: Enjoy full privacy in this charming city apartment (it's not just a room!) Welcome to this cosy 60-square-meter space with an industrial vibe, with typical Dutch touches and vintage items. Perfect for 2-4 guests. It includes a bedroom for two, a spacious living room with a sofa bed (for two), and a bathroom with a shower and toilet. The apartment is right next to the city center, and just around the corner there’s a small park.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is in a quiet street and literally next to the house is a little park with a playground and a children's farm - very unique in Amsterdam! Also very nearby is the Bellamyplein, a cosy small square which in summer is a favourite hang out for parents with small children because of a little pool.

In our neighbourhood (Old West) are a lot of good restaurants and coffee bars, for example in our street the delicious Italian restaurant "Spaghetteria". At the end of the street starts the authentic Ten Kate Market. The newest addition to the area's hip dining scene is "De Hallen Amsterdam". A centre for culture, food, fashion and crafts which recently won the Geurt Brinkgreve Bokaal 2014, a prestigious price for architecture and heritage. Within a 5 minute walk you enter "De Hallen" with a movie theatre, gallery, library, Local Goods Store, bicycle store, and so on, and the great "Foodhallen" where you can enjoy a large variety of delicious bites and drinks.
host_about: Hi, we are Bart en Nathalie. Bart is a film director, and Nathalie creates documentaries and art exhibitions. We love Amsterdam city life and the forest around our forest house in the east of the Netherlands. Feel welcome; we’re happy to share tips on the best spots in the neighborhood!

De Jordaan
The Jordan is an extraordinary area to stroll through the picturesque and maze-like streets. Visit one of the many art galleries or have a drink in one of the typical Brown cafés in this neighborhood like ‘Café Nol’ and listen to the sing-a-long Amsterdam folk songs.

Every Saturday you will find the Lindenmarkt (a general market) on the Lindengracht and a biological food market on the Noordermarkt. Mondays a flea market is organized at the Noordermarkt. And don’t forget to visit the Anne Frank House, where she lived with her family for 2 years in the annex of the building at Prinsengracht 263.

name: Luxurious Amsterdam home with canalview & garden
description:
An apartment with a spacious living room, luxurious kitchen, large bathroom, and delightful sunny garden.

The master bedroom is equipped with a king-size double bed and a wardrobe.

neighborhood_overview:
Our house is located in an ideal central location in Amsterdam.

The lively neighborhoods of De Pijp, Oost, Rivierenbuurt, and even Zuid are all within walking distance.

You can reach the city center within just 15 minutes by tram, which stops less than 2 minutes' walk from our house.

Cycling is even faster. This is our personal preference ;)

We are happy to share all our tips with you, so you can make the most of your stay in Amsterdam!

name: Private 4 Bedroom Ensuite
description: Enjoy some exxtra privacy for your and your friends in our private 4 bed dorm at the Flying Pig Downtown Hostel. Our 18th century building has been transformed into one of the most notorious party spots in the Dutch capital. Complete with a private ensuite bathroom, reading lights, USB ports and lockers under your bed to store your things, this is the perfect spot for young backpackers to base themselves.
host_about:
Our Flying Pig Downtown hostel is the place to party in Amsterdam with the 18th century building having been transformed into one of the most notorious party spots in the Dutch capital. We host awesome DJ’s and epic themed parties boasting an indoor smoking area with a pillow stage! 

Located in the heart of the city centre next to Amsterdam Central Station, you will also find Dam Square, The Anne Frank House and the bustling Red Light District just a short stroll away. Our hostel also provides free use of the guest kitchen, luggage storage, free Wi-Fi, a book exchange and a buffet style continental breakfast available everyday for only €5!

Known for our wild nights and a relaxed atmosphere during the day, we’re a popular spot for young backpackers to base themselves. There’s a reason we were rated the Best Hostel in the Netherlands in 2013 by TripAdvisor!

name: All private, city center @ homestay Wendie
description:

★ Room - Private, Bathroom, Balcony, Cosy & Comfortable
★ Safe & peaceful
★ Internet connection - Fast enough for business & Amsterdam...

Be Aware:
- The 3 stairways keep you fit but are steep

neighborhood_overview:
Our house & your room is located in the city center, where you can enjoy being part of daily life in one of Europe's most relaxed but exciting places. Once you've closed the door you're right in the middle of this buzzing city - feel the spirit!

- Next to Leidseplein and Kerkstraat.
- Two minutes from Paradiso, Melkweg, Jimmy Woo, Sugar Factory; name it!
- Five minutes from Jordaan & 9-streets shopping.
- Five minutes walk from Reguliersdwarsstraat.
- Seven minutes from Museumsquare.
- Ten minutes from Anne Frank house.
- An endless choice of restaurants, theaters at walking distance!
- There are bike rentals available around the corner.
- Tram and bus connection to all parts of the city and country.
host_about:
Wendie & her daughter Dana gratefully appreciate daily live in their wonderful 19th century house in the center of Amsterdam. 

Wendie has a background on the field of social cultural work. At the moment she works with people with dementia. She also designs and creates stained glass and Tiffany objects; her own design and in commission.

Dana is a student and also works in a restaurant run by children.

name: APARTMENT WITH CANAL VIEW!
description: Cees&Co is a beautiful canal house apartment in the center of Amsterdam. Only 5 minutes walk from Dam square, the big central shopping street Kalverstraat, 1 minut walk from Anne Frank's house and lots of other must sees this great city has to offer.
neighborhood_overview:
The magic of Amsterdam
Amsterdam’s Jordaan area is probably the most famous neighbourhood in the Netherlands. Once home to the working class and immigrants, the area now has become one of the city’s most picturesque and charming areas. The Jordaan is a great area to stroll around and discover why everyone is always raving about the neighbourhood. Maze-like streets offer a wide variety of hidden courtyards, cafés, restaurants, art galleries and pleasantly nosy neighbours. One also has access to some of the more scenic outdoor markets in the country (Noordermarkt). These are all within a walking distance. Just ask us for any suggestions.

When you’re a real adventurer, we advise you to rent a bike. It is very easy to get around from A to B, but watch out for the one-hand-on-the-steering-wheel-Amsterdam-mommies though. They are everywhere and come in large numbers. We have a bicycle rent out next door! From our location the Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh museum, Stedelijk Museum,

neighborhood_overview:
The ship is moored in the marina of IJburg. Characteristic of IJburg is that it's located on an archipelago of artificial islands in the IJmeer. As a result, the ship is right next to (or should we say in) the IJmeer, and makes you simply a few minutes away from beautiful nature reserves. The swamp forest 'Diemer Vijfhoek' is a well-known one, where the alternation of wetlands, open water and reed lands make it a true bird paradise. You can walk here from the boat in 20 minutes.

Fort Island Pampus is a stone's throw from the venue. The ferry service to Pampus departed just around the corner.

Craving an adventure a bit more far away? Polder IJdoorn and Vuurtoreneiland are located slightly to the north of the location and can be reached via Zeeburg. Here you can walk beautifully and enjoy the unique flora & fauna.

Still looking for the crowds? Amsterdam is less than 20 minutes away.

neighborhood_overview:
You’ll be staying in the vibrant Oud-West district, an up-and-coming area with a growing array of activities and services in recent years. Most buildings were constructed in the early 20th century, and today it’s one of the city’s most bohemian neighborhoods, with designer shops, brunch spots, and specialty coffee houses, as well as a wide range of entertainment options.

Leidseplein, just 350 meters from the hotel, is the nightlife hub of the neighborhood, with restaurants, bars, nightclubs, cinemas, and theaters. This area of Amsterdam also features artisan and gourmet food markets at the cultural space De Hallen. Not to mention that the city’s green lung, Vondelpark, is just 300 meters away, offering 47 hectares, including the Openluchttheater, an open-air theater hosting free performances every summer.

description:
This light 50m2 apartment with terrace is situated in the lovely hustle and bustle of the popular area the "Pijp" where you can hang out where the locals do, while being within walking distance from Amsterdam's main attractions.

I'd be glad to give you recommendations and tell you about all the good places!

neighborhood_overview: The Pijp is the best known of the working-class quarters built in the late 19th century. Harsh economic times necessitated a plan of long, narrow streets, leading to its apt nickname, 'the Pipe'. High rents forced tenants to sublet rooms to students and artists, lending the area its bohemian character. Today, the Pijp is home to a mix of halal butchers, Surinamese, Spanish and Turkish delicatessens, and restaurants offering authentic Syrian, Moroccan, Thai, Pakistani, Chinese and Indian cuisine. This makes the Pijp one of the best spots in town to buy quality snacking treats, the many ingredients for which are almost always bought fresh from the single largest daily market anywhere in the Netherlands: Albert Cuypmarkt. Over the years the local young creatives and fashionable have settled in the area, which results in lots of lovely boutiques, concept stores, bars and restaurants opening up everywhere. The 'Gerard Doustraat' has recently been declared to be one of the most upcoming stre

neighborhood_overview:
‘Baarsjes’ area and Amsterdam
The neighborhood (‘de Baarsjes’) is an upcoming area in Amsterdam and hosts a lot of new and trendy bars, restaurants and lunchrooms on every corner and a daily fresh market nearby. Public transport is just 500 mtrs. away and will take you in less than 10 mins. to the city center. Be sure not to miss the ‘de 9 straatjes’ (‘9 streets’) for trendy and one of a kind shops, walk around the Jordaan area and visit the Anne Frank Museum or take a canal boat for a unique view of the city. You will find the largest park of Amsterdam, the Vondelpark, nearby the apartment for a nice stroll and for some coffee and pie in the ‘Blauwe Theehuis’.

description: This great apartment on the quiet Bloemstraat (Flowerstreet) is located right in the most beautiful neighborhood of Amsterdam called the Jordaan, where most city hotspots can be found within walking distance! The apartment is luxuriously fitted for 1-2 people, ideal for couples or a business- or hollidaytrip. A fully equipped living room, bedroom, bathroom with shower and bath and complete kitchen will be at your disposal :)
neighborhood_overview:
A supermarket, all kind of restaurants like Mediterranean, Indonesian, Chinees, Thai and even Dutch cuisine, are all within walking distance. (and than we mean, no more than 5 minutes walk!) Also all kind of little shops and a laundry are around the corner.
Our canal apartment is in the most beautiful neighbourhood of Amsterdam: the Jordaan. The Jordaan is a district in the citycenter of Amsterdam, known for its beautiful houses, nice restaurants and original shops. When in Amsterdam, it is a must to stroll through the little streets and canals in the Jordaan. On the many bridges over the canals, you can take beautiful pictures and see why Amsterdam is called the Venice of the North.

Our apartment is close to some interesting hotspots:
- Anne Frank House (5 minute by foot)
- Rijksmuseum (20 minutes by foot)
- Van Gogh Museum (22 minutes by foot)
- Red Light District (15 minutes by foot)
- Heineken Experience (26 minutes by foot)
- Houseboat

description: Small room with double bed in shared apartment. Modern kitchen available for home cooking if needed.
host_about:
ABOUT ME
A single Norwegian living in Amsterdam, I have a steady job and my own apartment with a guest room. I like hosting guests from all over the world, and have done so lots in the last few years. I'm a huge nerd who loves science and science fiction, and am very curious about the world around me. I like learning new things, making new friends and generally try to experience as much as I can. 

INTERESTS
I go to a gym, train kendo, do archery and pistol shooting. I like to go to concerts (all kinds of music), to cinemas (all kinds of movies), to play games (like chess or backgammon or poker, also more advanced board games), and to read books (all kinds, but sci-fi a big favorite). 

FAVORITE BOOKS
I read mostly sci-fi, fantasy and crime books, and a fair amount of non-fiction too, mostly science and atheism.

name: Beautiful 1BR Apartment @ Jordaan (City Center)
neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is a picturesque neighborhood in Amsterdam, renowned for its narrow streets, charming canals, and historic buildings. Located west of the city center, the Jordaan was originally a working-class area, but has since transformed into one of the city's most desirable and trendy neighborhoods.

Characterized by its cozy, village-like atmosphere, the Jordaan is a maze of narrow alleys and hidden courtyards, lined with independent boutiques, art galleries, and a diverse array of cafes and restaurants. The area is particularly famous for its traditional Dutch "brown cafes," where locals and visitors alike gather for drinks in a warm, convivial setting.

The Jordaan's cultural significance is highlighted by several notable landmarks, including the Anne Frank House and the Westerkerk, a stunning 17th-century church with a prominent bell tower offering panoramic views of the city. name: Spacious & Sunny Apartment @ IJburg | 4 guests
neighborhood_overview:
IJburg is a modern and vibrant neighborhood located on a series of artificial islands in the IJmeer, just east of Amsterdam. Known for its innovative architecture and waterfront views, IJburg offers a unique blend of urban living and natural beauty, with plenty of parks, beaches, and canals creating a relaxed atmosphere. This area is especially popular with families and professionals, providing a balanced lifestyle close to nature yet well-connected to the city.

One of IJburg's highlights is its easy access to Amsterdam Central Station, reachable in about 15-20 minutes via tram or bus. This convenient connection makes IJburg an ideal spot for those who want to live in a quieter, more spacious area while still enjoying a quick commute to Amsterdam’s bustling center. The neighborhood also features a variety of amenities, including shops, cafes, and schools, as well as cultural and recreational spaces, making it a highly attractive place to live.

name: Generator -  Deluxe King
description: Experience comfort and style in our Deluxe King Room at Generator Amsterdam. Relax in a spacious king-sized bed while enjoying treetop views of Oosterpark. This room includes a private en-suite bathroom with a walk-in shower, fresh towels, and complimentary toiletries. A hair dryer is also provided for your convenience. Perfect for couples or solo travelers, our Deluxe King Room offers a peaceful retreat in the heart of Amsterdam, combining modern design with natural beauty.
host_about: Generator Amsterdam is located in the up-and-coming eastern side of the city, overlooking Oosterpark. This former zoological university building can accommodate 564 guests in 168 twin and quadruple rooms, with en-suite bathrooms and incredible views of the surrounding area. There is also one luxury apartment for six people, with views of the park and a self-catered kitchen. It has flexible and spacious social areas, filled with creative design touches like glass-fronted elevators, a light and airy café and an outdoor terrace. We’ve turned the former lecture hall into an impressive chill-out lounge and bar, while the old library is now a relaxation and private events room. The basement and café are now dining destinations and the original boiler room has become a secret late night bar.

neighborhood_overview:
The citycenter and the peaceful countryside are both close by.

Our B&B is located in a quiet, safe and pleasant street with trees. The neighborhood is known for the modern architecture of the residential houses.
At the end of the street, 60 meters from our house, there is a good restaurant with a terrace where you can have lunch and dinner, or enjoy a cup of coffee or a drink.
Opposite the terrace is natural bathing water with a bathing jetty. At the other side of the pedestrian bridge a large park begins.
For groceries you walk 10 minutes or you go one stop by tram. There are all kinds of shops and on Saturdays there is a food market.

The center of Amsterdam is within easy reach. Tram 26 departs every 5-10 minutes to Central Station (12 min.). The stop is a 3-minute walk away.

name: Perfect location apartment, pijp
neighborhood_overview:
De Pijp is brimming with fantastic (typical Dutch) cafés, restaurants, coffee shops and bars. Of course, a visit to Amsterdam wouldn’t be the same without a trip to the famous Albert Cuypmarket, flanked by over 100 shops. If you wander down Albert Cuypstraat and Ferdinand Bolstraat, the main streets in de Pijp, you'll find many exotic and authentic Syrian, Moroccan, Surinamese restaurants, to name but a few, and a typical Amsterdam pub is located on almost every corner. Also in abundance are the Islamic butchers, Surinamese, Spanish, Indian and Turkish delicatessens and grocery stores.

It's easy to find your way in this area!

name: Beautiful Loft by the Amstel
neighborhood_overview:
Wibautstraat is home to a variety of exciting bars and restaurants such as Bam Bao, Rijsel and many more. Volkshotel is on the same street as the studio and has a rooftop bar / restaurant, as well as a secret basement bar. The Student Hotel is a two minute walk from the studio - there, you can have cocktails, pizzas and play a game of pool or ping pong. Both hotels also frequently have a variety of events on!

There is a supermarket (Albert Heijn) located five minutes away by foot, as well as numerous bike rental shops.

name: Prachtig, groot huis in het centrum van de stad
description: This stylish, very spacious house is unique because of its central location on the Vondelpark. It is most suitable for large families.
neighborhood_overview:
We have lived in several beautiful places in Amsterdam, but this is our favorite, ideal location. That's because of the lovely spacious, bright and cozy house, where everyone feels right at home and welcome. Second, its central location is perfect. It has the statity of the chic Oud-Zuid and the liveliness of Oud-West.
The neighborhood has everything you want in Amsterdam. The streets surrounding the Vondelpark are beautiful with many trees and stately houses. You will walk right into the Vondelpark for a nice walk and a nice cup of coffee or lunch on a beautiful terrace. All the major museums (Van Gogh, Rijksmuseum, Stedelijk Museum) and the famous Concert Hall are within a 10-minute walk, as are the upscale P.C. Hooftstraat where all the big brands sit.
If you walk a little further, you are already in the popular De Pijp district, full of restaurants and cafes.
If you walk the other way, you'll be in Oud-West, one of the nicest and liveliest neighborhoods in Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview:
The houthavens is upcoming and Amsterdam's most wanted neighbourhood!

The area itself is an architctoral highlight located next to the IJ and still breathes the harbour vibes, but meanwhile new buildings are appearing. A unique combination in Amsterdam! It is still under development, but soon it will even had canals. All buildings are unique and archotectoral walks are being organised. The neighbourhood is childfriendly, has bars and restaurants and a park with lots of kids entertainment (and drinks for parants). Walk along the IJ and watch the ships sail by.

The houthavens form one neighbourbood together with the folcloric Spaarndammerbuurt where the 'Amsterdamse School' is the dominant architectoral style. The Spaarndammerbuurt is pure, cosy, colourfull and has shops, supermarkets, bars and restaurants and lots of playgrounds.

neighborhood_overview: Oud-Zuid is a well-to-do neighbourhood in the centre of Amsterdam. It is a largely residential district, characterised by the 1920's Dutch art-deco style housing, called Amsterdamse School. A number of the city's famous museums, such as Van Gogh, Stedelijk and Rijksmuseum are housed here, as is the Royal Dutch Concerthall, home to the world-renowned Concertgebouw Orkest. The area also has ample options for wining and dining, through its characteristic coffee houses, (brown) cafes and the many restaurants and it has several boutique shopping streets, including our own address, that attract high-heeled shoppers from around the country.

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is a neighbourhood of the city of Amsterdam, Netherlands. It is part of the borough of Amsterdam-Centrum. The area is bordered by the Lijnbaansgracht canal to the west, the Prinsengracht to the east, the Brouwersgracht to the north and the Leidsegracht to the south. The former canal Rozengracht (now filled in) is the main traffic artery through the neighbourhood.
Originally a working-class neighbourhood, the Jordaan has become one of the most expensive, upscale locations in the Netherlands. It is home to many art galleries, particularly for modern art, and is also dotted with speciality shops and restaurants. Markets are held regularly at Noordermarkt, the Westerstraat (the Lapjesmarkt textile market) and Lindengracht.

neighborhood_overview:
This area is known as the cosiest in Amsterdam. It is characteristic, alive yet peaceful and just plain lovely. It is called DE PIJP. It has everything you could wish for: beautiful old architecture and lanes to walk, bigger and smaller supermarkets just 3 minutes walk, restaurants and cafes 1 minute walk, lovely shops with interesting things and clothes. It is called the 'Quartier Latin' of Amsterdam. Lots of museums and tourist spots in walking distance or easy to reach by tram. The Center of the city is just 15 minutes walk or 6 minutes with the metro.
1 train and 1 metro-stop away from the Airport (travel-time 20 - 30 minutes).

description: Experience luxury in Amsterdam’s chic IJburg neighborhood. This 22m² room offers the comfort of a junior suite with a double bed, lounge area, and work desk. neighborhood_overview:
Discover Muiderlaan, Amsterdam

Muiderlaan is a vibrant, modern neighborhood in Amsterdam’s IJburg district, known for its striking architecture, waterfront living, and relaxed atmosphere. Surrounded by canals and close to the IJmeer, it offers stunning water views and plenty of outdoor activities, including walks along the marina and relaxing at the city beach, Blijburg. The area features trendy cafes, diverse restaurants, and unique boutiques, creating a lively yet peaceful vibe. With excellent public transport connections, including direct trams to Amsterdam Central Station in just 20 minutes, Muiderlaan blends urban convenience with a tranquil, coastal lifestyle — a perfect retreat for work or leisure

description:
Welcome to our charming nocarz nestled in the heart of Amsterdam, offering a unique blend of convenience and comfort for up to four guests.

Situated in a prime location, our nocarz is just around the corner from the tram stop, making it easy to explore the city's attractions.

With high ceilings measuring 3.5 meters high, our nocarz offers a sense of space and openness. Enjoy the luxury of your own private entrance and bathroom, providing both privacy and convenience during your stay.
neighborhood_overview:
The Rozengracht area in Amsterdam is a vibrant and dynamic neighborhood that offers a perfect blend of historic charm and modern convenience. Located in the Jordaan district, one of Amsterdam's most picturesque and sought-after areas, the Rozengracht is known for its lively atmosphere, diverse eateries, and unique shops.

Staying in a side street off the Rozengracht means you'll experience a quieter, more residential vibe while still being close to the action. The neighborhood boasts a rich history, evident in its beautiful canal houses and narrow streets. You can explore a variety of local boutiques, art galleries, and cozy cafes, each offering a taste of Amsterdam's unique culture.

Food lovers will appreciate the wide range of dining options, from traditional Dutch cuisine to international flavors. The area is also home to several popular markets, including the famous Noordermarkt, where you can find everything from fresh produce to vintage treasures.

neighborhood_overview:
Our house is right on the edge of the city centre, in the OOSTERPARK area, with it's own vibe and sparkle.
We are close to the zoo (Artis) and just around the corner you find the Oosterpark, the Tropen Museum, relaxed bars (Javastreet area) good food and the famous Windmill Brewery 't IJ.
The Dapper market is our daily market for fresh vegetables, cheese, fish and bread, and also fabric and clothes. Every day between 10-16, not on Sundays.
Several supermarkets around the corner, on the First van Swindenstraat (open from 8-22) and a night shop on Linnaeusstraat (open until 01:00).
host_about:
Once I stayed in a tiny room in the heart of Tribeca, NYC. Outside the window, squashed between brick walls stood a tall tree "planted by Yoko Ono". A memorable sales pitch for a queen-size bed on top of the world. 
Living on Wooster Street I was a local for a week, a fantastic experience. I would love to offer this kind of experience to my guests when staying in Amsterdam.

The house is mainly occupied by me, my son and Bonnie the cat, but we love to entertain friends and family with food and stories, so the house can be quiet as well as very lively. A family home in short ;-)

Our room for rent is on the second floor of a 4 story house, and with it's own bathroom on the same floor, it is all rather private and relaxed, for the guests as well as us. We live on the two top floors, just a shout away if any help is needed. 
My personal interests are art, photography, film and design, and I love to show my guests the local hotspots. New shows and exhibitions, exciting places to go for shopping, coffee or food, I am happy to share if you want to know.
 
I travelled west as far as San Francisco and east as far as Varanasi. Both ways there was always a 'friend's connection' to help out with local stuff. This was before nocarz existed, and now through this organization I can maybe be that connection for you.
Happy to help.

In daily life I am a professional creative.

neighborhood_overview:
Bos en Lommer, also known as BOLO, is an upcoming neighbourhood just west of Amsterdam's city centre within the centre ring.

It has all the good stuff, good public transportation, affordable parking (Q-Park Bos en Lommer), affordable places to eat, 3 supermarkets (Albert Heijn open until 22 pm), a few clothingshops, a library, 2 gyms, a bike shop, all within 2 minutes walking distance.

Restaurants to have diner nearby:

Buurman&Buurman (nice pizza's!), Podium Mozaiek, Tokio Sushibar (great sushi for delivery at home), Snackbar FEBO (try the frikandel and kroket!), Thai food (Kratiam), Turkish food (Bir Tat), Italian (Michelangelo & Domino's Pizza), Café Zurich and the newly opened Tajine Bar on Mercatorplein and of course the KFC across the street.

A nice hotspot in Amsterdam for foodies is 'The Foodhallen' at Bellamyplein 51 only a couple of stops with tram 7 (get out at Ten Katestraat). A great food experience!

neighborhood_overview:
Oud-West was a district of the municipality of Amsterdam in the Dutch province of North Holland from 1990 to 2010. As of 1 May 2010, it merged into the new West district.

The (former) district Oud-West is bordered by the Singelgracht (the border with Amsterdam-Centrum), the Vondelpark (the border with Amsterdam-Zuid), the Kostverlorenvaart (border with former district De Baarsjes) and the Hugo de Grootgracht (border with former district Westerpark).

The district, which grew from the nineteenth-century expansion districts along the Overtoom and the Kinkerstraat, had a population of 31,741 in 2003 and an area of 1.70 km².

Although there were (in 2007) 177 nationalities, Oud-West is not considered a "black" district. The political debate is limited to innocent topics such as whether trees should give way to create safe cycle paths, and the way in which the former Tollensstraat tramway depot had to be renovated.

name: Charming house with sunny garden
description:
Perfect for families with one or two young kids!

Located in a very charming and green residential area in Amsterdam-Noord, my house is a great place to come home to on your holiday.

With two sunny gardens, a comfortable couch, a spacious kitchen, a tub, a large attic full of kids toys, and a brilliant coffee place right around the corner, you'll feel right at home.

From my house, it's a 7 minute bike ride to the free ferry that takes you to the city center and beyond.
neighborhood_overview:
My neighborhood is called Tuindorp-Oostzaan, which translates into "Garden Village". It consists of very cute houses and is very green. It's right behind NSDM (7 minute bike ride) where the free ferry takes you to the city center.

Having said that, the north of Amsterdam is the most upcoming and cool neighborhood of the city. You don't need to go anywhere else. Cool restaurants, clubs, coffee places and markets are all around.

Be sure to check out my travel guide with Amsterdam-Noord tips!

description:
This amazing 3 floor town house is the perfect base for your trip to Amsterdam. Located only a couple of minutes away from the city centre, in a lovely area with architectural highlights and beautiful harbor views over the river IJ. You will have easy access to all of Amsterdam's major sights!

Comes with private car garage and secluded roof terrace. Close to public transport (tram, bus, ferry). Centre of Amsterdam, Artis Zoo, Muziekgebouw aan 't IJ, Eye Filmmuseum are a stone's throw away.
neighborhood_overview: The house is located in the popular Eastern Docklands district, close to the city centre. The area is surrounded by the water of the river IJ, which creates a very open and spacious feel to it. The neighborhood is famous for it's modern architecture, combined with the typical Amsterdam cosiness, with everything you need and more: cultural hotspots, green parks, city beaches, cosy bars, great restaurants and all the stores, supermarkets and services you'll ever need. It's a very popular area among locals: a quiet, hip and friendly neighborhood and at the same time very close to the hustle and bustle of the city centre.

name: Luxury Canal Suite De Heren
description:
Luxury Canal Suite De Heren has a fantastic location in the heart of the historic canals of Amsterdam.
The property is close to a number of famous sights:
The Anne Frank House, Royal Palace, the Rijks and Van Gogh museum are within walking distance.
neighborhood_overview:
Luxury suite De Heren is located on one of the most beautiful and original canals in the center, the Herengracht.
In the middle of the central canal belt, which has been on the UNESCO World Heritage List since 2010, De Heren offers a great location in the shopping heart of Amsterdam.
Located in the middle of the "Nine Streets", full of original shops and restaurants: an ideal base for discovering the Netherlands' most vibrant city.
The major attractions such as the Rijksmuseum, the Royal Concert Hall, the flower market and the Anne Frank House are all within a few minutes walking distance.
Famous nightlife spots, cafes and the city's top restaurants are also very easy to reach.

name: Spacious and well equipped apartment at Westerpark
description:
Welcome to our spacious double floor apartment of 82m2 with roof terrace and balcony. The apartment is situated on the 3rd and 4rd floor of the building and very light.

It's recently renovated and well decorated with vintage style attributes and modern art paintings. The vivid colors give it a warm atmosphere. You will definitely feel at home and have a perfect basepoint to discover the Amsterdam. It's just a small strall to Westerpark and the Jordaan. Bars and restaurants are close by.
neighborhood_overview:
The ambiance of the "Staatsliedenbuurt" is truly charming and enchating. You can see the families on the multicolor bicycles with baskets driving around or happy couples walking and enjoying the romantic Amsterdam's canals. Nevertherless, it is a wonderful location for an apartment in Amsterdam.

The first thing to do is to explore the charming streets of the area. Actually, this part was called 'Statesmen neighborhood' because the streets were named after the famous statesmen of 18th and 19th century. Just by crossing the river, you will reach Jordaan district, one of the oldest and, in the same time, the most unique part of the city. The Westerpark with its nice bars and restaurants is just around the corner.
host_about: Michiel, 39 years, from Amsterdam, the Netherlands living together with Marianne. Frequently travelling around for work or fun. Lived in Ethiopia, now based in NL.

neighborhood_overview:
The Nieuwmarkt neighborhood is extremely charming and quiet but right behind Nieuwmarkt square is the extremely busy Red Light district...
The fleamarket is 5 min away, Rembrandtsquare 10 min and Damsquare and Central Station 15 min, walking this is.
There are millions of restaurants around, Hemelse Modder on Oude Waal has a good price/quality level, Capteyn a bit further on the corner, simple but decent food and for Thai go to Snackbar Bird on the Zeedijk, funny name, tiny place but excellent food.
The restaurant in De Waag, the historical building on Nieuwmarkt offers a great surrounding and the food is fine too.
host_about:
I am from Amsterdam, or better I moved here from the south to study psychology at the university, but spent all my life in the musicbussiness, mainly running a musicvenue, called the Milkyway (Melkweg) till five years ago. Since then I operate as a consultant in the cultural field. I am a board member at several musicfestivals in the Netherlands and an advisor for the number one musicvenue in Budapest, A38.
So I travel regularly between the two cities and from december 2016 started  to rent out my new apartment in Amsterdam through nocarz.
My music collection in Amsterdam is a reflection of my taste and thanks to Spotify I do not have to take it with me when I travel!

neighborhood_overview: YAYS Amsterdam North by Numa offers an authentic experience. The northern part of the city boasts captivating views over the Amsterdam waters. The neighbourhood is well-connected by public transportation, so you’re just a short ferry or metro ride away from Amsterdam Central Station. EYE Filmmuseum and A’Dam Tower can be found near the closest ferry stop, both attracting tourists and locals alike. At NDSM Wharf, you'll find several hip cafés, art galleries and IJ-Hallen, the largest flea market in Europe, which is organized once a month. Despite its industrial history, the area has a warm and cosy charm, and became a highly sought-after neighbourhood to live in.

name: Amsterdam center Room Herisson
description:
THE ROOM
The room is about 17 square meters with a comfortable double big bed, a small table, a microwave, a coffeemaker and a refrigerator. Easy access to toilet and shower. Toilet and shower shared with the owners.
The apartment is situated on the ground floor along the canal.
neighborhood_overview:
THE LOCATION

The apartment is located in the oldest, UNESCO protected part of Amsterdam, with quite narrow streets. You could easily forget that you are right in the center of Amsterdam. This is the best place you can wish for while visiting Amsterdam!
Public transportation stops are right around the corner, but actually you don’t need it. You can reach everything in the center by foot, the rest by bike, which you can rent at our place for only 8 euro.

Within 5 minutes walking distance:
+ Nieuwmarkt (lively square, terrace, cafés and restaurants, Saturday there is an organic market and Sunday antiques)
+ Waterlooplein (daily brocante market)
+ Supermarket and organic supermarket
+ Rembrandt house (this is where he lived and worked. You can see it from your window!)
+ Opera house and city hall (together the ‘Stopera’)
+ Hermitage museum
+ Artis Zoo
+ Botanical garden Hortus Botanicus
+ Rembrandt square
host_about:
A friendly and relaxed person interested and curious about people.
I like to travel and work out.
IT, Circular economy and Sustainability is my passion.

The neighborhood is known for its varied shops, boutiques and cozy cafes and restaurants. Whether you're looking for trendy boutiques, local artisanal shops, or international cuisines, you'll find it all in the immediate vicinity.

name: Comfortabel app. dicht bij Westerpark en Jordaan
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located west of the city center, in the neighborhood "De Baarsjes" on the edge of the beautiful Jordaan.

It offers a great retreat from the busy streets of the city center, but you are not far away: there are plenty of buses and trams nearby to take you anywhere in Amsterdam. In 10 minutes by bike or tram, or 20/30 minutes on foot you are in the middle of the city center (with the Jordaan even closer).

Around the corner there are many cafes, restaurants, bakeries, small shops, a big supermarket and espresso bars. Also, you are within walking distance of both Erasmus Park and Westerpark (with a cinema, restaurants and cafes) and "de Hallen" (with a cinema, shops, eateries, etc.).

If you want to visit the beach you are on the perfect side of Amsterdam: it takes about 45 minutes in total to travel from the apartment to the beach of Zandvoort aan Zee.

name: Home at the Park
description: This B&B is located on the ground floor of a characteristic and solid mansion built around 1900. It's located right at the Oosterpark with easy access to all Amsterdam has to offer. This family friendly B&B with rear yard has two floors with the private area containing 2 bedrooms, bathroom and separate toilet. Guests can use the game room with pool and football table and garden room with many boardgames. There is also a private outside seating area which is rare for Amsterdam.
neighborhood_overview:
East of Amsterdam is a hip and edgy neighbourhood. It's a lot more authentic to Amsterdam and the locals than some other areas. It has many nice cafés and places to eat.
The center, Amstel and Central Station and De Zuidas are quickly and easily accessible. Shops for daily groceries (and more) at the Linnaeusweg, Middenweg and Beukenplein are right around the corner. There is a market for fresh and cheap produce 6 days a week (Dappermarkt) close by. You can walk to the Amstel and of course the Oosterpark which is right across the street. You can cycle to the center or De Pijp in just 10 minutes. The Amstel is 5 minutes by bike, the Tropenmuseum is a 5 minute walk through the park, as is Artis (city Zoo).
host_about: Having been an avid traveler myself, I now love hosting people here in Amsterdam. I have just re-listed my B&B again. Hope you'll enjoy your stay!

name: Clean comfy private studio in De Pijp central
description:
Beautiful and characteristic B&B studio with private bathroom, toilet and kitchenette on the second floor at the back side of an old Dutch building (1886) in vibrant neighbourhood 'De Pijp', central Amsterdam.

RAI conference center can easily be reached within 15 minutes.

The studio can be reached by the communal staircase of the house.

This studio is for two people only and not suitable for children and infants under 12 years old.

The property has solar panels and is listed energy label A
neighborhood_overview:
The studio is located perfectly in vibrant area 'De Pijp'. On the left is the romantic Sarphatipark, with in its 'Liefdesbruggetje' (lovers bridge).
Since 1880 lovers would show each other, and the neighbourhood, that they are an item. To the right is the Albert Cuyp market, Hollands longest market.

'De Pijp' is without doubt a melting pot of cultures and nationalities. It is brimming with fantastic cafés, culinary restaurants, coffee shops, supermarkets and bars. A heaven for foodies!
The nearest supermarket, Albert Heijn, is a 2 minute walk.

Within walking distance from the studio you will find popular sites such as the Heineken Museum, the Van Gogh Museum, The Stedelijk museum, Vondelpark, The Royal Concert hall, Paradiso, Leidseplein and the Rijksmuseum. There is also a canal cruise dock opposite the Heineken Museum. The city center is a 15 minute walk away.

The studio is also close to RAI conference center.

Please have a look
host_about:
I love to travel and I know how important it is to have a comfortable, relaxing accommodation abroad for a fresh start to the day and a good nights sleep at night.

De Pijp is my favourite area of Amsterdam, I hope you enjoy it as much as I do :)

My partner and I welcome you to our home and are happy to help in any way we can. Just ask!

Breakfast included.

During the summer the nearby Tolhuistuin is a great place for intimate live music performances. Walk a little further and along he river IJ the architecturally striking EYE Film Institute catches your eye with four cinemas, a restaurant and a bar and amazing sunset views.

The A'DAM tower nextto EYE accommodates a cool bar, a high end, revolving restaurant overlooking the city and ... the highest swing in Europe on the rooftop deck with the appropriate name 'Over the Edge'.

The NDSM shipyard is a former shipyard located on the banks of the River IJ. It has become a booming industrial and cultural creative hotspot in recent years. The shipyard hosts festivals, performances, exhibitions a
host_about:
Having travelled extensively and enjoyed other people's hospitality, I like the idea of extending that same level of hospitality to other people. I work for a career coaching company, where we help people discover their unique talents and then to define in what position they can thrive by using these talents. 

In my free time, I go outdoors (swimming, hiking) and I love to travel. I frequently have friends visiting from abroad and I enjoy taking them around to undiscovered places in Amsterdam and beyond.

I look forward to welcoming you and hope that you enjoy your stay in this amazing city to the fullest!

neighborhood_overview:
Westerpark is a vibrant neighborhood located in the western part of Amsterdam, the capital city of the Netherlands. It is known for its mix of residential areas, cultural attractions, and recreational spaces, making it a popular place to live and visit.

One of the prominent features of Westerpark is the park after which the neighborhood is named.

The park is also home to several cultural establishments, such as the Westergasfabriek, a former gasworks turned cultural complex that hosts art exhibitions, festivals, markets, and concerts throughout the year.

Westerpark is also known for its vibrant social scene. The area is dotted with trendy cafes, restaurants, and bars, offering a wide range of culinary experiences.

name: Unique guest suite close to CS and Jordaan
description:
The apartment is located on the lower floor of a typical Amsterdam 'canal house' (Dutch: Grachtenhuis) dating back to 1665. In the characteristic place you will find everything you need for a comfortable stay in Amsterdam. There is separate bedroom with 2 comfortable beds
. The living space includes a modern bathroom and a television. I am sure you will enjoy it during your stay in Amsterdam!
neighborhood_overview:
The house can be found on Realeneiland, a small island that is part of the city centre of Amsterdam, but slightly hidden away from the rest. The realeneiland is part of a group of three islands that together are called 'The Western Isles' (Westelijke eilanden), the two other isles being Bickerseiland and Prinseneiland.

The Western Isles are among the oldest areas of Amsterdam and have a rich history. The house itself is actually one of the fourteen original 'captain's houses' (kapiteinswoningen) of Realeneiland.

The house carries the name 'In 't Anker', which translates as 'in the anchor'; the name along with the house's symbol can be seen on the gable. It can be found on the Zandhoek - the name for the street and corner of the island. As you walk around the neighbourhood you will see boats everywhere, as the island also functions as a small city harbour.
host_about:

name: Spacious and trendy 2-br loft with huge terrace
description:
Enjoy vibrant Amsterdam from our comfortable and spacious loft apartment. The property is completely renovated and accommodates all your needs for a memorable stay.

Start your day in zen-mode in the yogastudio on the ground floor, get the work done in the study room equipped with great wifi, discover Amsterdam's most popular areas on walking distance, master the BBQ with a good bottle of wine during sunset on the 56m2 terrace and sleep like a baby in the spacious hotel-like bedroom.
neighborhood_overview: The vibrant 'Baarsjes' in Amsterdam West is a very centrally located neighbourhood with lots of great boutique shops, restaurants and bars. There's an Albert Heijn (supermarket) right next to the apartment and. The Ten Kate market is also perfect for shopping at 10 mins walking distance. Multiple parks are just minutes walking away, like Erasmuspark (with a nice bar), Rembrandtpark and Vondelpark. The city centre of Amsterdam is at 10-15 mins walking distance, or 5 mins by bike or tram (stop in front of the house). Paid parking is possible around the corner.
host_about: Already live in Amsterdam for 10 years and think it's genuinely the greatest city in the world! Together with my wife to be we live in Oud-West, an amazing area for enjoying Amsterdam for a short or long period. We both love traveling and enjoy offering other people a peak of the great life we live in this lovely neighbourhood. If we're not at home we're probably exploring other parts of the world, while enjoying good food and some kitesurfing or skiing where possible. Feel free to get in touch!

neighborhood_overview:
Atmosphere, the Quartier Latin of Amsterdam.

Welcome to de Pijp.
This apartment is located on a nice square in this trendy neighborhood in Amsterdam.
There is a tramstop in two minutes walking distance, and parking places in front.

De Pijp is brimming with fantastic (typical Dutch) cafés, restaurants, coffee shops and bars. Ofcourse, a visit to Amsterdam wouldn't be the same without a trip to the famous Albert Cuypmarket, flanked by over 100 shops. If you wander down Albert Cuypstraat and Ferdinand Bolstraat, the main streets in de Pijp, you'll find many exotic and authentic Syrian, Moroccan, Surinamese restaurants, to name but a few, and a typical Amsterdam pub is located on almost every corner. Also in abundance are the Islamic butchers, Surinamese, Spanish, Indian and Turkish delicatessens and grocery stores.

name: Appartement in de Pijp
description: My apartment is in the heart of the Pijp, one of Amsterdam’s most vibrant neighborhoods. A 15-minute walk takes you to the bustling core, full of bars and restaurants, though I prefer the quieter hidden spots. It’s also 15 minutes from the city center, though we locals rarely go, as it has become too touristy. Bordering the charming East and steps from the Amstel River, the apartment offers a peaceful retreat in the quiet Diamond Neighbourhood, with the buzz just minutes away.
neighborhood_overview: De Pijp is the most vibrant part of Amsterdam. In the narrow streets of this hip district you will find numerous restaurants with kitchens from all over the world, but also classic Amsterdam pubs and cafes with terraces outside. The Albert Cuyp Market is my favorite spot of the Pijp. Here you can still find the real “Amsterdammer”. It is a melting pot of all the nationalities that Amsterdam is rich and there are also many tourists to be found. Try a herring (or stroopwafel for the sweet chews) here. Sarphatipark is also nearby. A cute park that features English gardens with ponds and lawns. Enough to see and do so!
host_about: Hi, I’m an “import-Amsterdammer” and have completely fallen in love with this city. I’m passionate about traveling and love learning new languages and discovering different cultures. During your stay, I’m happy to share my favorite spots and tips to help you experience the best of Amsterdam. I look forward to sharing my love for this city with you!

description: Not too large, not too little. Just cosy enough to bring back those PJ-party memories. Each comes with bedding, an en-suite bathroom, multiple power outlets and luggage lockers. We have four 4- bed dorms in the following themes: Cheese, KLM, brothel and Bike.
neighborhood_overview:
Cocomama has quite an interesting history. Believe it or not, but before we turned it into the city's first (and only) boutique hostel, it used to be a well-known brothel. We kept the marble entrance, royal round staircase, original chandeliers and high ceilings in place – the rest we let go of (sorry guys).

We're only one block away from the Albert Cuyp market, Europe's largest daily open-air market. We (and our wallets) love the stalls – offering anything from fresh produce, Dutch street-food, to the latest in fashion (well girls, not sure about the last one, but it's definitely fun to have a look around).

Tram-stop, supermarket, museums, cafés, restaurants, canals, park – anything one needs when visiting Amsterdam is on a stone's throw away. It's as central and easy as it gets.

neighborhood_overview:
De Pijp is located directly south of Amsterdam's city centre and it is part of the borough Amsterdam-Zuid, in a part of the city known as the Old South (Out Zuid). Most streets in De Pijp are named after Dutch painters, like Jan Steen, Frans Hals, Ruysdael and Vincent van Gogh. Nieuwe Pijp and Oude Pijp are districts in the area.

The most famous and busiest street market of the Netherlands, the Albert Cuyp Market, is in De Pijp. It is open six days per week and attracts many tourists. The former Heineken brewery is also a popular tourist attraction. Next to the former Heineken brewery is the Marie Heinekenplein, which has a number of bars and cafes. Along the canal 'Ruysdaelkade' there is a small red light area.

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is a district in the citycenter of Amsterdam, known for its beautiful houses, nice restaurants and original shops. When in Amsterdam, it is a must to stroll through the little streets and canals. On the many bridges over the canals, you can take beautiful pictures and see why Amsterdam is called the Venice of the North. Popular streets in the Jordaan are the Prinsengracht, the Westerstraat, Haarlemmerstraat and the '9 straatjes' (nine little streets).

In the Jordaan you can visit different types of markets. Every Monday till 13:00 there is a flea market at the Noordermarkt. It is the perfect place to buy old-fashioned Dutch plates, pots and linen. There are also many stalls selling clothes and leather accessories. To find the best treasures, make sure you are early!

For food you can go to the Lindenmarkt at the Lindengracht on Saturdays, or to the market on the Westerstraat on Mondays. Every Saturday there is a biological food market at the Noordermark
host_about: A proud B&B owner, dog lover and a real dutchie loving live in living the Jordaan area with my husband :)

name: Sweets hotel - Gerben Wagenaarbrug
description: Sit on high! A soaring 3-storey bridge house close to Amsterdam North’s favourite bars and cafés. Cocoon in this colourful bridge house with a view of the boats moored on the North Holland canal. This is the largest of all our bridge houses, including a living room, bedroom and bathroom. This bridge house is a perfect overnight stop for cyclists on the LF7 cycle route. Amsterdam Central Station is accessible by a short walk (12 minutes) and a ferry ride (6 minutes).
neighborhood_overview:
Bridge house Gerben Wagenaarbrug is located in Amsterdam North - a neighbourhood that has become increasingly popular over the past few years. With free ferries crossing the river IJ and the new North-South metro line up and running, it is faster and easier than ever to get to Amsterdam centre. But why would you, if there's so much to do and see in Gerben Wagenaarbrug's vicinity? All places popular with locals are within a 15 minute walk. Visit the EYE Film Museum and the A'dam Tower, or taste colourful beers at
the Oedipus Brewery. Check out our city guide for more recommendations!

This bridge house is classed as NOISE LEVEL - MEDIUM.
host_about:
SWEETS hotel is a one-of-a-kind hotel located across Amsterdam in 28 different bridge houses. Each bridge house has been transformed into an independent hotel suite that accommodates a maximum of two guests.

For centuries, Amsterdam’s bridge houses accommodated the city’s many bridge keepers who were responsible for opening the impressive structures for passing water traffic. With building dates between 1673 and 2009, the bridge houses carry an extensive history. Visiting them in chronological order is like a journey through time: their various architectural styles reveal how the city developed and grew, when new quarters were built and even how people thought about city development at that time.

With the hotel room interiors, SWEETS hotel offers guests a unique and comfortable living space, while keeping the history of every bridge house in mind. All bridge houses are different, and so are the interiors. Every SWEET accommodates up to two adults and contains a kingsize double bed, a bathroom and coffee and tea facilities.

SWEETS hotel, first initiated in 2012 as an urban space project, is 8 years in the making. Over half of the 28 bridge houses are currently available for reservations, with more coming soon.

SWEETS hotel is an initiative and co-creation of the architecture office Space&Matter (known for De Ceuvel, an ecological hub), project development partner Grayfield and Suzanne Oxenaar and Otto Nan of Seven New Things, founders of Lloyd Hotel & Cultural Embassy (the world’s first 1- to 5-star hotel) and Hotel The Exchange.

neighborhood_overview:
The Pijp is a vibrant and diverse neighborhood located in the southern part of Amsterdam, Netherlands. Known for its bohemian atmosphere, rich cultural diversity, and lively street scene, it has become one of Amsterdam's most popular and sought-after neighborhoods

Cultural Melting Pot:
The Pijp is a true cultural melting pot, home to a diverse mix of residents, from young professionals and families to students and expats. This blend of cultures and backgrounds gives the neighborhood a unique and cosmopolitan vibe.

Foodie Paradise:
One of The Pijp's standout features is its culinary scene. The neighborhood is teeming with an array of cafes, restaurants, and food markets, making it a true food lover's paradise. You can savor a wide range of cuisines, from Dutch and international to trendy vegan and fusion options. The Albert Cuyp Market, the largest outdoor market in the Netherlands, is a must-visit for fresh produce, street food, and local treats.

name: Canalhouse in the Center
description:
This beautiful canal house is a charming place conveniently located in the heart of Amsterdam’s Canal District near 'Het IJ'. The estuary where during the Golden Age, merchandise and spices were supplied and stored from all corners of the world.

The canal house is situated within walking distance of the main museums, popular shopping areas, and historic landmarks.

The house is just renovated and geüpgraded in January 2024.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the city center of Amsterdam. It only takes 5 minutes by foot to arrive to the Waterloopsquare.
It’s 15 minutes walking to the Red light district and the famous Rembrandtsquare. 20 minutes walking to the Central station.
At the Waterloopsquare and Rembrandtplein you find the nearest supermarkets, shops, pubs, coffeeshops and restaurants.
Also in the direct area of the house you can find some nice bars and restaurants.

The nearby Foeliestraat reminds us of the latter, a spice that has been loved since the Middle Ages and is better known as nutmeg. Walk with us through the area.

In the 19th century, the neighborhood was a refuge for Jews who had fled the pogroms in Eastern Europe. They had already been preceded by Sephardic Jews who had been expelled from Spain and Portugal since 1492. The Portuguese synagogue is still a reminder of them, which for a long time was considered the largest synagogue in the world.

name: Nice apartment in Oost with garden!

neighborhood_overview:
The area, the Indische buurt, is a lovely vivid area, but nice and quiet at night. It's located close to the center, it's just about 10 minutes by tram or bike.
In the neighborhood you can find several nice cafes, restaurants and parks. There is also a small cinema right across the street and you can find a known market on walking distance, called the Dappermarkt. A famous beer brewery, Browerij 't IJ, is not too far away either! By bike or tram it's just a matter of minutes (2 stops) and i guess it's about a ten minute walk. Especially in summer their terrace is crowded and a lot of fun!
A little bit further away is the zoo, Artis. If you take the tram 14 to the city center you will pass by Artis.
host_about:
Hi! I'm Carry, a 35 year old woman from Amsterdam, The Netherlands. I love to travel and I take every opportunity I get to go abroad! Besides traveling I enjoy being with friends, food, weight training, biking, nature, hiking, metal smithing, baking sweets and lots more.

In 2010 I have traveled through South America as a backpacker together with my sister for about 10 months and fell in love with the continent, especially with Argentina and Buenos Aires. I have been going back yearly and recently lived there for a couple of years as well. 
In 2016-2017 my sister and I lived and traveled in New Zealand with a working holiday visa, so that was another great adventure where we used nocarz regularly :)

I like to join this platform both as a host and a guest. When possible, I offer my apartment in Amsterdam to fellow travelers during my own holidays.

In my profile I said I speak Spanish, because I do understand most of it. I'm far from fluent though, especially my speech isn't good!

In case I’m abroad either my mother Regien or sister Belle will be your host and handle both the check-in and check-out. In that case their contact information will be available to you after booking.

If you have any questions feel free to ask, I'll be happy to answer :)

name: Nice,new app. nearby Center/Jordaan
host_about:
I’m 38 years old and I live in Amsterdam for more than 10 years now. My boyfriend (Thomas) and I bought this totally renovated apartment 10 years ago. We love our house because of its central location and the nice view over the water of the Da Costakade. It feels like a private lake just in front of our door. When the sun comes out our garden-side balcony is the perfect place for a morning breakfast and coffee. And in the afternoon we often enjoy a glass of wine on our French balcony on the other side of the apartment, watching many boats come by on the canal. 
Last summer we discovered the Amsterdam canals with our own private boat. Being near the water or on the water is one of the most relaxing things you can do in this city (there’s a boat rental nearby if you would like to try).  We also enjoy cooking and dining at home or somewhere else in the city. If you are interested I can give you some nice tips for sightseeing, shopping, the best coffee place, bakery and dining places in the neighbourhood.
I hope you like it as much as we do!

neighborhood_overview:
De Baarsjes is a vibrant and dynamic neighborhood in Amsterdam West, known for its diversity, trendy cafes and restaurants, and a mix of historic and modern architecture. The area is located west of Amsterdam's city center and is well-connected by public transportation, including trams and buses. Cycling is a popular way to get around thanks to well-laid-out bike paths. The neighborhood also has easy access to the A10 highways, making it ideal for drivers.

De Baarsjes is renowned for its multicultural population and lively community. This is reflected in the variety of dining options, shops, and cultural events held throughout the year. There is a strong neighborhood community that prides itself on its inclusive and welcoming atmosphere.

name: Beautiful apt in city center for FAMILIES ONLY
neighborhood_overview:
The Amsterdam Canal District is a neighborhood in Amsterdam, Netherlands. The seventeenth-century canals of Amsterdam, located in the center of Amsterdam, were added to the UNESCO World Heritage List in August 2010. The Amsterdam Canal District consists of the area around the city’s four main canals: Singel, Herengracht, Keizersgracht, and Prinsengracht. From Brouwersgracht, the canals are generally parallel with one another, leading gradually southeast into the Amstel river.

Many of the canal houses in the Amsterdam Canal District are from the Dutch Golden Age in the 18th century. Many of these buildings, however, underwent restoration or reconstruction in various centuries, meaning that these building display many different architectural styles and facades.

name: Amsterdam Farm Lodge: quircky, old farmers style
description:
Experience this 'off the beaten track' accommodation just on the outskirts of Amsterdam. 'Amsterdam Farm Lodge' is a haven for those seeking a sustainable stay, offering a basic but comfortable and spacious accommodation. Nestled within the innovative urban farming project, 'NoordOogst', the lodge offers an escape from the city's hustle and bustle without straying too far away from its joys.

Please note that we're not located directly in the city center so check our location before booking.
neighborhood_overview:
We are on the site of an awesome urban farming project, you'll find fields with crops, pigs, chickens, a restaurant, a veggie take-away, kids daycare, natural play ground, woodworking, natural playground, a beekeeper, a wine yard and a brewery. And plenty of space to play.

The hustling and bustling NDSM wharf with is only 15 minutes away by bike, from here the ferry to Central Station departs. Ten minutes biking to the other side you can find nature area 'het Twiske' where you can swim, bike and hike. Only 10 minutes by foot you can discover the hidden nature area of 'Noorder IJplas'. The Zaanse Schans, IJselmeer, beach and 'bollenstreek' are easy to reach.
host_about: We are a couple from Amsterdam and we love to travel. A few years ago we've hosted a wintersport chalet in Austria. We liked it so much that we wanted to open our own B&B. Nice to know: each of the streets in the Jordaan is named after a flower.

name: Sleeping in a Church - 9m2 Compact Room at Bunk
neighborhood_overview: After just minutes on the free ferry from Central Station, you’ll find Amsterdam’s true north. This up-and-coming neighbourhood is alive and kicking, bursting with cultural hotspots. At the centre of the neighbourhood’s social life there was always the Saint Rita church. Now that it is home to Bunk Amsterdam, this still holds true. Locals and travellers alike come to catch some rays on our terrace, sticking around for an affordable dinner and some free cultural nourishment.
host_about:
BUNK bridges the gap between hotels and hostels by combining affordable luxury rooms and smartly designed private bunk beds.
We converted two monumental churches into meeting places for travellers, locals and artists alike. We host inclusive social events in our sustainable restaurant and other communal spaces.

We aim to redefine hospitality by creating a place for communal wonderment. Where those who wander will start to wonder, triggered by true art, honest food and sincere smiles. We make comfort and design available to everyone, without the need for deep pockets. BUNK is where you can feel free to be your wonderfully weird self as you play your part in new stories you can take home with you.

You're surrounded by vibrant cafes shops and the outdoor market, with metro, trams, and buses just around the corner. Please respect the neighbors; no parties allowed.

name: Sonder Park House | King Suite
description:
Museums, thrift shopping, and stroopwafels — your Amsterdam experience begins at Park House. Each room includes a coffee maker, space to work, and an HDMI-equipped television for streaming. To unwind, we love the cozy lounge and calming garden terrace.

In the Oud-Zuid neighborhood, there’s plenty to discover. The iconic Rijksmuseum is home to the best of Dutch art. And Vondelpark hosts seasonal outdoor concerts at the Openluchttheater. Enjoy a picturesque stay at Park House.
neighborhood_overview: Oud-Zuid is the best-kept secret in Amsterdam. And we're giving you the scoop. Bordering the historic center, this trendy neighborhood has the ideal combination of upscale boutiques and memorable museums. Spend your day relaxing in the beautiful greenery of Vondelpark, listening to music spilling from the open-air theater. Or stroll down charming tree-lined streets to admire the stunning 19th-century mansions. Ready for some shopping? Check out P.C. Hooftstraat. Formally named after a Dutch poet and playwright, this luxurious street is home to countless designer stores including Gucci and Dior. After a day of discovery, indulge in one of the many global restaurants and cuisines scattered throughout.
host_about: Rooms, suites, and apartments in over 40 cities around the world. Every Sonder features designer details, keyless entry, and fast free WiFi. Experience a better way to stay today.

name: 17th Century Flowermarket Apartment
neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam is a city born for biking and walking. There are many sights to explore in the surroundings, such as the Flower market (50 m), Leidsestraat (220 m), Nieuwe Spiegelstraat art galleries (400 m), Rembrandtplein (450 m), The 9 Streets shopping district (650 m), Leidseplein (750 m), Royal Palace at Dam Square (850 m), the Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum and Vondelpark (1 km) and the Anne Frank House (1,7 km). Central Station is located at 2 km, RAI Amsterdam (4,8 km and 15 min by taxi) and Schiphol Airport is at 15 km from the property.

The nearest supermarket (Albert Heijn at Koningsplein) is only 2 minutes away and the tram lines 1, 2 and 5 are the same distance. Trams 4, 9, 16 and 24 do stop at Muntplein and are at 3 minutes walking distance. In the center of the buzzing nightlife, several bars, LGBT venues, restaurants and two Pathé cinemas (including the historic Art Deco movie theater Tuschinski) can be found within a radius of 200 m.
host_about:
Dear traveler,

I'm Saskia and together with my partner Michiel we offer our lovely apartment up for rent.
We are a nice couple with no kids and no pets. We love to travel ourselves and because of the great experiences we had staying in b&b's, we love to give that in return for other travelers.
We hope you have a great stay at one of the most beautiful places in town.

Regards,
Saskia and Michiel

neighborhood_overview:
De Baarsjes lives! It is the neighborhood where you can find all kinds of trendy cafes, restaurants and coffee spots just outside the city center.

Most of the hotspots are located along Jan Evertsenstraat and around Mercatorplein, an area where the hipsters of Amsterdam like to spend their sultry summer evening or lazy weekend afternoon drinking. Popular spots include neighborhood bar Baarsch or the always cozy Le French Cafe on the corner, where you can sit on the water with your wine. You can also eat well from breakfast to dinner. As with the somewhat hidden Cafe Cook, where in addition to the cozy living room atmosphere, you also have all day sun on their square terrace. Great!

If you are looking for a quiet place? Rembrandtpark and Erasmuspark are just around the corner.

neighborhood_overview:
Within a minute walk you will reach the popular Van Woustraat with restaurants and cool grocery stores like 'Marqt' and 'Landmarkt' shops like 'Stach' and Hutspot (a must visit). Within a 5 to 10 minute walk you will find one of the most popular areas in Amsterdam 'De Pijp' with a vibrant restaurant/bar area, a park and the famous Albert Cuyp market.

Rent a bike, cycle along the canals, visit the Rijksmuseum, the Anne Frank house, 'De negen straatjes', galeries, the red light district or many other cultural sights. name: Enjoy ShipStays Hotel in Amsterdam!
description:
Make your trip unforgettable!

Whether you enjoy the sun on the back deck, pass the time on the middle deck with parlor games, or dare to climb onto the mast with a safety belt and enjoy the unique view from the top, there really is something for everyone here!

Welcome Aboard! :)
Beautiful house with a upstairs bedroom and spacious living room with open kitchen! Massive doors to the garden with BBQ and lounge set. Perfect for couples to enjoy the real Amsterdam life.

Experience Amsterdam like a local on this typical cozy Amsterdam houseboat! Very comfortable and close to the center and popular locations like Brewery 't IJ (beer brewery+bar), Natura Artis Magistra (zoo), Café-Restaurant De Plantage. A lot of fun things within walking distance and a tram stop just around the corner. Guests will have acces to their own private bedroom and private bathroom. You will enjoy this place because of the great location, the beautiful view and the unique experience.
neighborhood_overview: The Oostelijk Havengebied is an urban residential area in a water-rich environment (in summer there is plenty of swimming). The area borders the center with, among other things, the lively Czaar Peterstraat (in 2015, the best shopping street in the Netherlands). With lots of small companies from the creative sector, workshops, coffee shops and restaurants. Within walking distance are 'Panama', the 'Lloyd Hotel', shopping mall Brazil, Amsterdam Roest, Theater Fabriek Amsterdam and Amsterdam Convention Factory, Brewery 't IJ and the Funenpark. The old center and Central Station are a few minutes by bike. You are also at tram 26 in three stops at the Central Station. Tram 10 to Artis, Rijksmuseum and Leidseplein stops around the corner. The A10 ring road can be reached in a few minutes via the Piet Hein tunnel. From the Zeeburgerkade there are numerous hiking and hard routes possible. Rent a SUP board or a sloop around the corner and discover Amsterdam from the water!

neighborhood_overview:
Combine the magic of Amsterdam with the serenity of this tranquil location, renowned for its avantgarde architecture!
IJburg is one of the safest, most stress-free spots in Amsterdam, 12 minutes by tram from the center, the tram going often. The house is on one of the loveliest streets of IJburg, with practically no traffic at all; all you hear at night are the ducks in the canal down below. There’s a picturesque little harbour at walking distance with trendy restaurants and bars as well as a park and two beaches. One of the beaches has a bar/restaurant.

name: Cozy apartment near the park and city centre
description: The house is characteristic and has all the comforts. Located in a quiet but typical Amsterdam street in East district. Close to the cozy Beukenpleintje and parallel to the Oosterpark. The house is easily accessible by Public Transport and within a few minutes you can walk across the Amsterdam canals with a stroopwafel in your hand. ❤️
neighborhood_overview: One of the most popular areas in Amsterdam. Near to the park, canals, Amstel river, Artis, and other famous spots in the city center.

description:
Our cozy yet elegant residance is centrally located in the heart of Amsterdam Oost, from which you can perfectly explore the city.

One of the standout features of our apartment is the rooftop terraces, which offer stunning views.

Inside, you'll find all the amenities you need for a comfortable stay. The apartment is thoughtfully equipped with everything from a fully functional kitchen to a luxurious bathroom, as well-appointed living and working spaces that will make you feel right at home!
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood has a lot to offer and is vibrant and colorful. As soon as you step out the door and walk down the street, you immediately immerse yourself in the bustling city life with plenty of cozy shops, boutiques, coffeehouses, bars, restaurants, deli shops, cinema's and much more. There's something for everyone. Additionally, both Oosterpark and Flevopark are just around the corner. There are many attractions within walking distance, such as the Tropenmuseum and Artis Zoo. By bike, you can reach the city center within 10 minutes!

description:
My apartment is very central, 15 minutes' walk from Jordaan, Vondel Parc, 20 min from important museums, very bohemian area!

It is very large (93 m2), very bright and quiet.
Your room measures 20 m2, large windows overlooking a garden, absolute tranquility.
The bathroom has a shower and a bathtub.
I am French but have lived in Amsterdam for a long time and can guide you in your choices of outings, restaurants etc.
Prohibited drugs!
Am vaccinated against covid 19

description:
Lovely renovated apartment along the river, across Amsterdam Central Station.
Peaceful neighborhood and a great getaway from all the city noise. The free ferry boat, which is a few minutes away by foot, takes you to the city centre in 3 minutes!

Everyone who comes to this place loves the vibe and energy! Perfect for a city trip.
Supermarkets within walking distance.
Cheapest parking area in Amsterdam!

name: Your beautiful home in fancy Amsterdam-South
neighborhood_overview: We live in Amsterdam-Zuid, arguably one of the safest and best neighborhoods in Amsterdam. The van Tuyll van Serooskerkenweg, the location of our apartment, is the most beautiful and greenest street in the area and is very close to the Museum Square, the Canals, RAI and Zuid As (Business) area.
host_about:
Hi! 

For more then 10 years, I live in beautiful Amsterdam. My passion for art is mainly created by my partner Erik, who is an art dealer and has a gallery as well. If you are an art lover, then its a must to stay in this apartment. We also provide an Amsterdam Art Tour Guide. Interested? Book and stay with us! :)
